You might find an alignment of the vision with Nim <a href="http://nim-lang.org/" rel="nofollow">http://nim-lang.org/</a> .  The have done a C backend as for their language, and the language appears to have the semantic properties you have mentioned...<p>from the site:<p>&quot;
...
•Macros can use the imperative paradigm to construct parse trees. Nim does not require a different coding style for meta programming.<p>•Macros cannot change Nim&#x27;s syntax because there is no need for it. Nim&#x27;s syntax is flexible enough.<p>•Statements are grouped by indentation but can span multiple lines. Indentation must not contain tabulators so the compiler always sees the code the same way as you do
